                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1123 Coltman, Charles/–: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-12-12T16:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 12, 1922—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 12—11:22 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>489. Charles Coltman, American merchant, was shot by Chinese soldiers in Kalgan,
                    afternoon 11th, after dispute as to his right to <pb facs="0826" n="710"
                        xml:id="pg_710"/> leave Kalgan in automobile with silver currency. Spinal
                    cord injured. May possibly live but paralyzed. Receiving best medical treatment
                    Peking. Report follows.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schurman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
